How to setup AWS Client VPN to access AWS Resouces from Laptop.

1.Clone the easy rsa repo
$ git clone
https://github.com/OpenVPN/easy rsa.git
$ cd easy
rsa /easyrsa3
2.Initialize PKI environment
$ ./easyrsa init pki
3.Create new Certification Authority (CA)
$ ./easyrsa build ca nopass
4.Generate the server certificate and key
$ ./easyrsa build server full server nopass
5. Generate the client certificate and key
$ easyrsa build client full client1.domain.tld nopass
6.Copy server and client certificates and keys to one directory
 $mkdir ~/demo
$ cp pki /ca.crt ~/
$ cp pki /issued/server.crt ~/
$ cp pki / server.key ~/
$ cp pki /issued/client1.domain.tld.crt ~/
$ cp pki /private/client1.domain.tld.key ~/
$ cd ~/demo
7. Upload the certificate and keys to ACM
$ aws acm import certificate certificate fileb://server.crt private key fileb://server.key certificate chain
fileb://ca.crt region ap south 1
$aws acm import certificate certificate fileb://client1.domain.tld.crt private key fileb://client1.domain.tld.key certificate chain fileb://ca.crt region ap south 1
